<answer>We know that the perimeter is the sum of the sides of $\triangle ABC$.
We can write an algebraic expression for the perimeter.
$AB+BC+AC=32$
We have the length of side $BC$.
$AB+12+AC=32$
It is given that $\angle ABC=\angle ACB$, so two sides must also be equal.
As you can see in the diagram, sides $AB$ and $AC$ are equal.
$AB+12+AB=32$
$2×AB=20$
$AB=10$</answer>

